De_LostTemple2 Source (10.09.08)
-----------------------------------------------
by StarD00d (d00ds.com)

Greetings:
----------
The good news is: de_LostTemple2 is finally released.
The bad news is: de_LostTemple2 will be the last CS:S map created by d00ds.com.
We supported CS:S for more than 3 years and had a lot of fun. Apparently you did aswell =)
But now it's time to move on. We are already working on different projects these days.

Huge thanks to all our fans and supporters!

See you in another game!

StarD00d & Magikus
d00ds.com


About:
------
This is the first release candidate of de_losttemple2, the 5th map of d00ds.com following de_rush, de_nightfever, de_cpl_fire and of course de_losttemple.
The temple, once a jewel of the mayan civilization, is located near a lake deep in the jungle. Beside the enemy forces you have to fight the mosquitos aswell. Smoke Grenades proved to be quite successful.

Story:
------
After the discovery of a very well hidden secret inside a forgotten temple archaeologists all around the world are eager for more discoveries.
This time they are at the right place to look for but don't know it yet. They presume an entrance to a hidden chamber at spot A. However there is another entrance at spot B still undiscovered.
A group of so called terrorists take their chance to make some quick profit. Little do they know there are special forces waiting in the area to turn the plan into a failure.

Layout:
-------
There are three main routes in the map: to the left a small temple at the cliff, through the swampy water in the middle directly beneath bomb spot A and to the right through the ruinous main temple hall. All three routes have in common that after taking over the hot spots the terrorists can storm both bomb spots. There is no specific A route or B route. However the counterterrorists can use three short routes to switch between A and B.

The map supports 40 spawns.

As always the map includes lots of custom textures, models, skybox and even sounds.

Performance:
------------
Despite the use of numerous vegetation models performance turns out very well.
3 GHz Radeon 9800 runs on 120 fps average and 95 fps for the worst spot.
For comparison the same system at dust2 runs on 110 fps average and 85 fps for the worst spot.
If you need more fps turn off the 3d sky with "r_3dsky 0".

Attention Server Admins:
------------------------
Since the map is larger than 16MB with all the custom content, put "net_maxfilesize 64" into server.cfg to allow download of the map.
However with BZIP2, it is from now on possible to compress large files which the players must download before being able to play (e.g. maps...) This way you can reduce the size of the de_losttemple2 download from 49MB to 28MB. Also the file gets downloaded from your fast webserver. That allows an enormous saving of time at the time of the remote loading.
Just follow these easy steps:
* Download the file "de_losttemple2.bsp.bz2" @ http://files.ingame.de/counterstrike/gameserver/cstrike/maps/de_losttemple2.bsp.bz2
* In your server.cfg set "sv_downloadurl http://www.yourURLgoeshere.com/cstrike". (insert your own domain name)
* In the public_html directory (default) of your webserver create a new folder "cstrike" and a subfolder "maps".
* Place the file "de_losttemple2.bsp.bz2" in the folder "cstrike/maps" on the webserver via ftp.
* Keep in mind you still need to install the map de_losttemple2.bsp on your gameserver as you would normally do.

De_losttemple 
-----------------------------------------------
by Magikus & StarD00d (d00ds.com)
presented by http://www.inHalflife.de by ingame

Description:
-----------------------------------------------
The central element of the map is the temple which can be reached using the crossing route from bombspot A to B. There are 3 ways for the terrorists as well as for the counter-terrorists. Looking from the CT spawn there is the left route to A and through the underpass. The central route leads through the water passing the bridge to the temple. The right route is leading through the hallway and to B (see overview picture).

We tried to create a very balanced map that is fun to play using elements that strongly dominate the gameplay, i.e. the water and the bridge, the hallway and the underpass with the crossing line trough the temple. 

Story:
-----------------------------------------------
An ancient and lost temple has been found. Archeologists discovered a great secret and are about to put the pieces together. Terrorists: Use the C4 to destroy one of the artifact puzzles the archeologists have already secured on A or B. Counter-Terrorists: Prevent terrorists from bombing the secured artifacts.

De_lochs version "2"
Map and cusotm textures made by Vig AKA Mark Dygert
Site: www.vigville.com/de_lochs
Email: vig@vigville.com

=========================


Install instructions:
--------------------------------------------
- Unzip de_lochs2.zip to your cstrike folder normally found in;
*X:program files\valve\Steam\SteamApps\yoursteamnamehere\counter-strike source\

Manual Install:
- Place de_lochs2.bsp, de_lochs2.nav, de_lochs2.txt inside your cstrike\maps folder.Normally found in:
 X:program files\valve\Steam\SteamApps\yoursteamnamehere\counter-strike source\cstrike\maps\

*or wherever you installed steam to, hopefully you know how to find the cstrike folder by either doing a search or you just know how to find it...



==========================
Contents:
-----------------------------------------------
- de_lochs2.bsp:
This is the main map file that also contains all the custom textures that Where used for the map.

- de_lochs2.nav:
This is the navigation file for the bots. I included it so you don't have to spend the 15 min setting up the bots for the first time.

- de_lochs2.txt:
This file contains the text you see at the beginning of the map. You know the text that no one reads?

The custom textures I created for this map have been compiled into the bsp file so there is no need for a res file. What a pain that was...

A special "thanks" ester egg room has been included in the map for who are adventerous enough to find it. 

There are a lot of changes, new routes, new places to hide, more detail. And above all I have optimized the holy crap out of the map using every trick I know how to use. I even used a few I had no clue could be done before =) It runs great all of the test machines, so if you encounter poor FPS it will be news to me =P

Title : de_lja_house
Description : A small custom defuse map for Counter-Strike Source
Release Date : 09 02 2007
Filename : de_lja_house.zip
Author : Tim Kitevski (Mapping) - Mail tim.kitevski@gmail.com

===================================================

* Installation *

Unzip the contents of the .zip (the folder named cstrike) into the Steam dir where Counter-Strike Source is location and overwrite the "Cstrike" folder
Note: Don't worry nothing will be overwritten I just put all the necessary files in the one folder so you can install them with one placement.

e.g. "C:\Program Files\Steam\SteamApps\USERNAME\counter-strike source\"


* Construction *

Build time: 
~ 5 weeks

Compile Time: 
~ 27 mins

Editor: 
Hammer 4.0

Map Known Bugs: 
None, but let us know if you find any.

New Models:
Tree models: Klaus Viehofer

New Sounds: 
crkets.wav - an ambient sound

Notes:
Map was originally made for a machinima/short film. The whole design is based of a persons' real house. The person was the writer/director of the short film, 
Lloyd Jones. After the project I decided to make it into a small Defuse map. 

There may be some performance related lag on lower end machines 
(Less than 2GHz CPU, Less than 1Gig Ram) as there is a relatively large amount of props in the scene. 

This is basically unchanged from the product for
the film (some minor alterations were needed for release as a playable map, but essentially it is how it was). 

It is only a small map and as such it only suits a max of 16 players (8 x 8).

DE_LITE_RC1 by cashed (released October 2010)

Well worked and interesting by layout bomb/defuse map by Ted 'cashed' McIlwain - author of widely known map de_season and the coauthor of very popular map de_greene. Here is a CSS-transition from one of the map versions for CS.

"Originally a level for Counter-Strike 1.6 competitive play, and created for ESEA and the community by myself. The original map idea was discussed by a panel of top players and community members to attempt a arena top pick. Knowing the restrictions for competitive mapping, I knew it would never get the justice it deserves on goldsrc engine. This rendition includes custom textures and models created by myself, and stock Half-Life 2 and CS:S assets." - from mapauthor's note at tedmcilwain.com

By the way the Fans of Counter-Strike 1.6 can find here at GameBanana FOUR versions of this map: de_lite_rc1, de_lite_rc2, de_lite20100110 and final version de_lite :-)

Despite Release Candidate state the map is absolutely playable also is well good designed!

About Playing with Bots: In original mapauthor's archive Navigation Mesh for playing with Bots was not included, but you can download separately the created from scratch, manually optimized (hand-tuned) and fully place painted NAV-file.
